edu.kit.cm.kitcampusguide.standardtypes
Class Category

java.lang.Object
  edu.kit.cm.kitcampusguide.standardtypes.Category
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Category
extends Object
implements Serializable

Represents categories. Stores the respective id, the name and gives functions to get categories. A category is used to both identify the type of a POI (p.ex. office or beverage machine), and to later filter by it. A category is only saved in the POIs and does (apart from id and name and all categories) not save any data. The list of categories saved in the categories is used to identify all existing categories. Each category (identified by the id) is represented by exactly one object. Therefore it is advised to initialize all categories either at once or from a single source. Initializing them this way can be done easily by calling the constructor, without any other actions necessary. If a persistent source is used for the categories, the IDs can be preserved over start and shutdown of the program.

fred

Constructor Detail

Category

public Category(int id,
                String name)
         throws IllegalArgumentException,
                NullPointerException
Constructs a new category. Adds it to the collection of categories. Therefore it just needs to be called once to initialize a category with the given id and name, which can later be gotten via the function getCategoriesByIDs or getAllCategories.

Parameters:
id - The ID the new category should have. Must be unique. However, this is not tested.
name - The name of the new category.
Throws:
NullPointerException - If the name of the category is null.
IllegalArgumentException - If the category created would have a duplicate ID.

getAllCategories

public static Collection<Category> getAllCategories()
Returns a collection of all categories. This categories are all for which the constructor has been successfully called.

Returns:
A collection containing all categories.

getCategoriesByIDs

public static Collection<Category> getCategoriesByIDs(Collection<Integer> ids)
Returns a collection of the categories with an ID in ids. If there are duplicate IDs all of the categories with that id are returned. However no guarantee is given for that in future versions. All categories for which the constructor has been successfully called will be taken into account for this list. Should best be used in combination with getID.

Parameters:
ids - A collection of IDs representing the categories that should be returned.
Returns:
A collection of the categories with an ID in ids.

Parameters:
id - an id
Returns:
the category matching the given id or null if no such category exists
